 AYO ESAN GOVERNOR Rotimi Akeredolu, on Thursday, April 1, 2021, began a 15-day working vacation as the first instalment of his 2021 Annual Leave. In a letter transmitted to the State House of Assembly and addressed to the Speaker, Rt. Hon. Bamidele Oleyelogun, Governor Akeredolu said the leave would commence from Thursday, 1st to Friday, 23rd April, 2021, both days inclusive. While Governor Akeredolu is away on vacation, the Deputy Governor, Lucky Aiyedatiwa, will perform the functions of the office of the Governor. The Governor will resume for duties on Monday, April 26, 2021.  